originalText.text: Very disappointed in the logistics of this event.  Event location changed with little notification, nothing VIP about the VIP tickets I purchased, and absolutely no communication regarding 3 course meal not available at new location!  As a diabetic, I manage the time for my meals and ended up ill because absolutely no food was offered or given when promised.  In addition, I ended up paying 11 bucks for a bottle of water and was hounded on by cast members for additional money throughout the show.  Only 3 queens throughout the show, very disappointing.

originalText.text: They must take down negative reviews because this was the worst! First of all, I prepaid $500 ($95 per person!!)for a VIP 3 course meal for 5 people for my daughter’s 25th birthday. When we arrived, we still had to pay an additional $22 EACH for a 2 drink minimum. The waiter informed us that there would also be a gratuity charged at the end of the “meal” (which was $65!) The meal consisted of salad that tasted like fennel filled grass and a burnt cheeseburger. So, I paid for a 3 course meal that was not three courses. The “VIP” table was a folding table that fell on us when we were seated. The show was eh as well. One of the divas didn’t even know the words to one of the songs! Beware of this place. We went because Lips had a pipe burst, but this place was not a good alternative. If I could get my money back, I would have. It was a complete rip-off. I would give it 0 stars if I could.

originalText.text:
First time at a drag show. We showed up an extra five minutes early and ended up at the very front! (Without paying for vip tickets)

I happened to be the only male-presenting member of the audience that night and definitely got an experience I won't forget. Wonderful venue.

originalText.text: Celebrated a birthday. We had a ball. Will definitely return! If you wondered what to do for a fun night out, this is what you need!

originalText.text: The show itself was okay, only 3 actual drag queens doing like 10 impersonations. They had their good moments but the show was not spectacular by any means. They made some really tone deaf and offensive jokes and references when impersonating Amy winehouse (a dollar bill in the nose, and jokes about staying away from needles). I understand it’s supposed to be “funny” but personally, I don’t think joking about mental health, substance abuse, and overdose is all that hilarious. Drink and food service was difficult, and overall this show and the company was badly run and overbooked (shows were basically scheduled on top of each other, and guests for other shows would show up in the middle of your show, leaving seating confusing and the place packed and making it impossibly for you to get out). Definitely not worth the $200 we paid, and would rather go back to Lips NYC (and I recommend you do too!)
